# http://www.mei.edu/content/article/unpacking-turkey-s-failed-coup-causes-and-consequences
Gulenists
- education, tolerance, peace
- strict hierarchy, operative secrecy, requirement for obedience
- extensive organization inside bureaucracy; capturing key positions to expand power & influence
prosecuted military opponents of Erdogan with fake evidence
prosecuted Erdogan himself, he reacted with dismissing thousands of Gulenist officials
who was it?
- after 2013, Gulenist military rose up in ranks, because kemalists were prosecuted by Ergenekon
- tortured soldiers confessed, that Gülen was involved in the coup
- the Coup portrayed itself as Kemalist, but Gulenists would have also done that to get support
- there is an overall consensus, that the Gülenists were it, but maybe in Coalition with some Kemalists and other anti-Erdogan officers
Purge after the coup
- 60,000 soldiers, police, judges, civil servants, and teachers have been suspended, detained, or are under investigation. 45,954 from the ministry of education
- 18,044 detained 
- 13,419 army officials, civil servants, and judges arrested
- roughly 40% of armys generals & admirals arrested
- all academics banned from travelling for academic purposes, 70,000 passports confiscated
- 3 news agencies, 16 TV channels, 23 radio stations, 45 daily newspapers, 15 magazines, 29 publishing houses shut down


