# Regime Change Turkey
Ein neues Regime überwindet das alte
- old order stays in place and can be used against those who oppose the change
- state meeting universal democracy standarts can still be undemocratic under circumstances (e.g. in turkey)
- new regime will adopt practices, outlook, and telltale apology from the old regime
Secular, liberal urbanites alarmed by change in regime discourse
- they believe in technocracy and missed the dynamics of populist politics
first five years the AKP got controlled by mil and civ bureaucracy
- bureaucracy got defeted only in 2011 - ergenekon(?)
2012 education reform - Gebetsschulen, Islamkurse
2013 Gezi-Park, 2.5 mio. Menschen
- AKP musste nicht resignen, wie früher der Fall gewesen wäre, weil schwaches Militär
- Police violence -> loss of international rep. and legitimacy
- AKP istanbul sagt "our liberal partners won't like what we are up to" (148)
- Im Dezember Korruptionsanklagen gegen Erdogans Söhne, loss of legitimacy
2014 Erdogan entlässt Großteil der Judikative, legitimacy staggered.
